					<h2 class="text">Everything social</h2>
					<p class="lede text">Facebook pages, Twitter analytics, Pinterest dashboards, Newsletter segmentation tools â everything Biagio needed to take his business into the world of social media, and watch it grow.</p>
					<p class="text">Social media presents a huge opportunity for retailers like Biagio, but needs fine-tuning to get right. Omnipresent social sharing options have kept his Facebook Page engagement well above his competition. Thanks to some responsive email templates, his newsletter â which has always reached thousands â now bears nearly eight times the industry average conversion rate. The result? More customers in store, more traffic online, and greater attendance at the regular special events Biagio holds. Which, of course, you can sign up for online.</p>

					<h2 class="text">Live <abbr title="Point of Sale">POS</abbr> integration</h2>
					<p class="lede text">In-store purchases are handled via the industry-standard Bransom retail system. The Bransom system keeps product prices, stock, and other properties in sync across stores, regions, and commerces.</p>
					<p class="text">In the fast-moving world of retail jewellery, Biagio needs to keep tabs on product stock at any given moment. If a diamond ring is sold in store, that has to be reflected instantaneously online. Tight integration was critical to Biagio's success as a retailer, so I partnered with Bransom to deliver a world-first Bransom-Lemonstand module.</p>

					<h2 class="text">Integrate everything.</h2>
					<p class="lede text">Biagio retails hand-selected fine jewellery from all over the world, but he doesn't stop there.</p>
					<p class="text">He offers a UK-first service: the ability to build your own jewellery. Using the Goldmark and Gemsone product catalogues â each containing billions of possible product combinations â customers at Biagio the Jeweller can build precisely the piece they need. I was tasked with building a system that allowed customers to do exactly the same thing online, without losing that 'in-store' brand feeling. Oh, and the prices across the Goldmark and Gemsone catalogues vary minute-to-minute, as they're linked to real-time mineral and metal cost indices.</p>
					<p class="text">Some creative thinking was needed: first up, I couldn't store this info in Biagio's database, but Lemonstand needed it to be. In collaboration with the Lemonstand CTO, we developed an entirely <abbr title="Asynchronous Javascript and XML">AJAX</abbr>-based technique for fetching live pricing data as the user requested it, and binding that data to the product upon submission to the cart. The result? That in-store jewellery-building experience, without having to leave the office.</p>
