					<h2 class="text">Maximum impact</h2>
					<p class="lede text">It's too easy to include too much. Elsa's site was designed to maximise her content, her personality, and her progress. The navigation was designed from a rigorous Information Architecture, typography designed for readability and consistency, and colour used for impact.</p>
					<p class="text">We're bombarded by information in our everyday lives. Somehow, we can make our way through it – but it's effortful, difficult. That's not what the web is for. Elsa's site features bespoke headline copy to draw in the user, site-wide components – like link-lines between pictures and text, and omnipresent social functions – to ensure a smooth, consistent experience. Animations were retained only when necessary. As with all good projects, I took a lot more out than I decided to keep in. The result? An easy-to-parse, perfectly-comprehendable way to access everything Elsa.</p>

					<h2 class="text">Social to the core</h2>
					<p class="lede text">Social media was central to Elsa's campaign, and I built it to be front-of-place.</p>
					<p class="text">The homepage features a beautiful cascading tweet wall that picks up on anything Elsa tweets, or is tweeted with the hastag #elsa2.4k. Next door, there's a gorgeous post wall that picks up on anything featured on Elsa's Facebook page. And, if you're happy to authenticate with the site, you can tweet and post right from the wall itself. Keeping you up-to-date with Elsa's goings-on without ever having to switch tabs.</p>

					<h2 class="text">Encouraging donations</h2>
					<p class="lede text">Elsa's campaign runs concurrently with Indiegogo, a crowdfunding site for independent projects. I wanted to integrate live campaign updates, Indiegogo donation options, <i>and</i> corporate sponsorship facilities on every page.</p>
					<p class="text">The omnipresent Indiegogo bar tracks Elsa's progress towards her targets. The omnipresent 'Donate' button hovers enticingly above her content (as well as elsewhere throughout the site). And, if clicked, supporters can donate via various payment providers – or get in touch with Elsa directly, if they're keener to donate through an organisation as a formal sponsor.</p>
